The paper introduces a new type of layer for convolutional neural networks that exploits symmetries, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of group convolutions also involves mathematical concepts related to algebra and group theory, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper achieves state of the art results on rotated MNIST, which is a task related to natural language processing (cs.CL).
